snippet.textDisplay: Just in case anyone is reading the comments who wants to breastfeed....having big boobs isn’t something to stop you from it unless it’s just not something you  want. My breast are huge. It WAS hard trying to feed my tiny babies, I felt like I was going to suffocate them with how big they were! BUT a lactation consultant should see you, at least one always comes to speak with you were I live, and mine told me right away that since my breast were so big it would be easier for me to nurse holding my baby like a football and it was So much easier that way. So I did football hold until baby was a little bigger. I’ve had 3 exclusively breast fed babies out of 4 kids and no shame in formula feeding bc fed is best but if you’re set on breastfeeding like I was just know that there’s so many ways to help you do so you just have to push hard, it doesn’t come easily for everyone but it’s worth it. I always talk to a lactation consultant at LEAST 3 times with each baby, they truly help so much! The first time I breast fed was HARD I barely got any sleep at all between feeding every two hours and pumping afterwards, my second was a little better and I got to breast feed a lot longer and this time around I’m over producing so I have a nice freezer stash. You can do it IF it’s something you really want ,sometimes it won’t be easy and there are some cases where you can’t because of medical reasons and I am in no way talking down on anyone.
